category.name: games
description:
Mafia (known also as 'Werwolf' in Germany) is a popular social psychological strategic game. There are two teams in the game playing against each other - citizens and mafia. In the beginning of the game citizens do not know who the mafia is, and their main goal is to find it out as soon as possible, since Mafia is acting as well.

The game is a huge fun to play! Apart from that, it teaches to recognize lie, persuade others and improves rhetorical skills overall.

A real game: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ll_I_BIdD5E

category.name: games
description:
Welcome to the Zürich D&D Meetup Group! <br>

Join our Discord server for more shaneanigans.

Calling all adventurers! Let's get together to play Dungeons and Dragons in the old fashion style, pen&paper and throwing dices. Started this group to meet other roleplaying enthusiasts who would like to form a group to get together and guide your characters through endless adventures.

<br>Dungeons and Dragons is the most popular tabletop role-playing game of all time. The game is played with about 6 players. One person takes the role of storyteller, AKA the Dungeon Master, and narrates the story in a medieval fantasy world filled with magic, monsters, romance, intrigue, and adventure. The rest of the players take on the roles of individual fictional characters and explore that world, often becoming heroes in the story. The story is like a completely interactive "choose your own adventure" book. Different shaped dice are used to determine the outcome of attempted actions. <br> <br>Scheduling games of D&D is a little more complicated than just showing up for a game. There are three different ways people assemble to play D&D. <br> <br>We have the "Introductory Games" meetups that will happen on Fridays and will help create new group of players who have no experience at all or already know about the D&D system. <br>We have the "Long Campaigns" meetups that will run several times per month in order to continue a Campaign (long adventure) with the same group of players. New players can join if someone steps down from the game. <br>We have "One-Shot games" where short adventures that normally take one or two sessions will be held. <br>
name: Dungeons & Dragons Zürich
organizer.name: Víctor González

category.name: games
description:
Every week we meet to play story games together. We meet from 5:30 until 10:00 on Tuesday's at the host's house in Central Luzern, about 5 minutes walk from the Bahnhof.

Anyone who enjoys collectively telling compelling stories together is welcome. Story games are similar to traditional roleplaying games, but they sometimes have no GM, and players have a bigger hand in making narrative decisions. But no prior roleplaying experience is needed--only enthusiasm and an open mind! We play in English but do not be intimidated if English is not your first language. We play one shots of indie games like:
The Quiet Year
Microscope
Fiasco
Apocalypse World
Fate
Ten Candles

The host supplies the space, snacks and any necessary dice or stationary for the game. Feel free to bring anything you want to munch on or games you'd like to try!
name: Storytelling Roleplaying Games in Luzern

description:
This group is for anyone that likes to play games or hang around while others are playing games :) In fact, game designers are also welcome. The whole idea is to get together and play games! So bring your favorite games and meet some people to share in the fun.

If you are interested in coming, don't worry about bringing games. Many people will bring some. If you'd like an idea of what kinds of games people bring, check out this website. It has a data bank of all kinds of board games so you can see if something there might interest you and maybe can request it from the group (keep in mind many on the top 100 are no longer in print)

Players range from casual gamers who come mostly just to have a good time and interact with others to more serious board game hobbyists.

description:
Culture Class CH <br>

Culture Class CH is all about appreciating and celebrating the diversity of life together. <br>

We do so by get togethers and having drinks in bars and clubs, but also with a handful at home. Moreover, we offer stage to exchange and learn something new. Learn about wine tasting, presentation skills, negotiation skills, or body language at home or somewhere else in an inviting atmosphere, followed (or accompanied) by some drinks. <br>

The fun of learning together won't get lost in too much seriousness. If you are having anything you would like to share, or any requests or suggestions: please contact Peter or Anna and we'll make it happen together!

<br> Culture Club CH workshops are powered by cultureclass.ch. Please 'like' us on facebook: www.facebook.org/cultureclass and we'll spoonfeed you with the best of social and clinical psychology, intercultural knowhow, and many other things worth knowing. <br>
name: Culture Club ZH

description:
Purpose: To promote the quizzing culture and regularly hold quizzes in Zurich 


Who should join: This is a group for anyone interested in trivia, facts, quizzes and to learn through fun games! As a keen enthusiast for learning, I felt there is no better and enjoyable way than 'quizzing'. This group encourages individuals or teams to conduct quizzes. 


Why:  The mind of a group is always greater than that of an individual. This group aims to have the members meet at a 'cool' place periodically and immerse in the fun world of  quizzing, trivial pursuit on any of the topics! 


What can members expect: Members can expect regular quizzes. A great opportunity to meet like-minded people and exchange knowledge, experience and have fun at different locations in Zurich!

category.name: games
description:
Chess4kids is expert in teaching chess to kids 4 years up. We work in a systematic and interactive way. Through our journey of teaching we developed a playful program that fosters children between 2 and 5 years. As a part of our learning program we integrate chess as one element out of many that supports the children on their way to explore their inner and outer world. Many studies show the profound benefits of chess and the effectiveness of learning through play like instill confidence, sharpen critical thinking, boost emotional intelligence, enhance arithmetic skills and strengthen academic performance. Our mission therefore is to extend those benefits and spread the word. This innovative MINIMASTER program incluses a huge variety of behavioral and interest based activities. During the classes we offer a stimulating and widespread learning enviroment with many sensory and movement related exercises and games. With this specially designed and innovatice program we cover every aspect of your child's development covered -- from social interaction to physical activity to cognitive learning through play. Through play, children will develop the confidence, creativity, curiosity and learning skills they need for school and beyond. Our MINIMASTER program is part of our chess academy as a prelevel of our MAXIMASTER program (for kids between 6 and 9). It consists of 2 levels: prelevel 1 and prelevel 2. Through that we can focus on the development areas of each defined age group. Since we work in small groups with experienced teachers, each child can grow on its individual pace.
Our lessons offer a safe, fun and nurturing environment for kids and include interactive moments, physical movements (like chessercizes as combinations of psychomotorical exercises and chess), storytelling and guidelines for game play at each level of development. The classes feature unique play based activities, games and more.
name: Chess4kids Minimasters Program 2-5 years

category.name: games
description:
Mafia (known also as 'Werwolf' in Germany) is a popular social psychological strategic game. There are two teams in the game playing against each other - citizens and mafia. In the beginning of the game citizens do not know who the mafia is, and their main goal is to find it out as soon as possible, since Mafia is acting as well.

The game is a huge fun to play! Apart from that, it teaches to recognize lie, persuade others and improves rhetorical skills overall.

A real game: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ll_I_BIdD5E

category.name: games
description:
Welcome to the Zürich D&D Meetup Group! <br>

Join our Discord server for more shaneanigans.

Calling all adventurers! Let's get together to play Dungeons and Dragons in the old fashion style, pen&paper and throwing dices. Started this group to meet other roleplaying enthusiasts who would like to form a group to get together and guide your characters through endless adventures.

<br>Dungeons and Dragons is the most popular tabletop role-playing game of all time. The game is played with about 6 players. One person takes the role of storyteller, AKA the Dungeon Master, and narrates the story in a medieval fantasy world filled with magic, monsters, romance, intrigue, and adventure. The rest of the players take on the roles of individual fictional characters and explore that world, often becoming heroes in the story. The story is like a completely interactive "choose your own adventure" book. Different shaped dice are used to determine the outcome of attempted actions. <br> <br>Scheduling games of D&D is a little more complicated than just showing up for a game. There are three different ways people assemble to play D&D. <br> <br>We have the "Introductory Games" meetups that will happen on Fridays and will help create new group of players who have no experience at all or already know about the D&D system. <br>We have the "Long Campaigns" meetups that will run several times per month in order to continue a Campaign (long adventure) with the same group of players. New players can join if someone steps down from the game. <br>We have "One-Shot games" where short adventures that normally take one or two sessions will be held. <br>
name: Dungeons & Dragons Zürich
organizer.name: Víctor González

category.name: games
description:
Every week we meet to play story games together. We meet from 5:30 until 10:00 on Tuesday's at the host's house in Central Luzern, about 5 minutes walk from the Bahnhof.

Anyone who enjoys collectively telling compelling stories together is welcome. Story games are similar to traditional roleplaying games, but they sometimes have no GM, and players have a bigger hand in making narrative decisions. But no prior roleplaying experience is needed--only enthusiasm and an open mind! We play in English but do not be intimidated if English is not your first language. We play one shots of indie games like:
The Quiet Year
Microscope
Fiasco
Apocalypse World
Fate
Ten Candles

The host supplies the space, snacks and any necessary dice or stationary for the game. Feel free to bring anything you want to munch on or games you'd like to try!
name: Storytelling Roleplaying Games in Luzern

description:
Willkommen zur Berner Brett- und Kartenspielegruppe. Wir sind eine Gemeinschaft, die sich regelmässig zum Spielen von Brett- oder Kartenspiele aller Art in einer Beiz oder bei jemandem zuhause treffen. Die Gruppengrösse variert je nach Anlass und Spiel zwischen 3-12 Personen. Wir spielen viele verschiedene Sachen, und immer auch etwas neues. Wir versuchen auch alle bekannten und öffentlichen Spielerunden in Bern und Umgebung bekannt zu machen.  

Hier findet ihr unsere BGG Guilde: https://boardgamegeek.com/guild/view/3116

und hier unsere Collection: https://boardgamegeek.com/guild/collection/3116?title=&subtype=&B1=Apply

Falls ihr eines davon mal spielen wollt meldet euch doch einfach beim besitzer des Spiels. 

Habt ihr selber einen Anlass in Bern oder Umgebung bei dem ihr noch nach Mitspieler sucht? Dan meldet euch doch beim Event Organisator. 

Neue Spieler und Spiele sind sehr erwünscht!!!

This group is for anyone that likes to play games or hang around while others are playing games :) In fact, game designers are also welcome. The whole idea is to get together and play games! So bring your favorite games and meet some people to share in the fun.

If you are interested in coming, don't worry about bringing games. Many people will bring some. If you'd like an idea of what kinds of games people bring, check out this website. It has a data bank of all kinds of board games so you can see if something there might interest you and maybe can request it from the group (keep in mind many on the top 100 are no longer in print)

Players range from casual gamers who come mostly just to have a good time and interact with others to more serious board game hobbyists.

description:
Culture Class CH <br>

Culture Class CH is all about appreciating and celebrating the diversity of life together. <br>

We do so by get togethers and having drinks in bars and clubs, but also with a handful at home. Moreover, we offer stage to exchange and learn something new. Learn about wine tasting, presentation skills, negotiation skills, or body language at home or somewhere else in an inviting atmosphere, followed (or accompanied) by some drinks. <br>

The fun of learning together won't get lost in too much seriousness. If you are having anything you would like to share, or any requests or suggestions: please contact Peter or Anna and we'll make it happen together!

<br> Culture Club CH workshops are powered by cultureclass.ch. Please 'like' us on facebook: www.facebook.org/cultureclass and we'll spoonfeed you with the best of social and clinical psychology, intercultural knowhow, and many other things worth knowing. <br>
name: Culture Club ZH

category.name: games
description:
Chess4kids is expert in teaching chess to kids 4 years up. We work in a systematic and interactive way. Through our journey of teaching we developed a playful program that fosters children between 2 and 5 years. As a part of our learning program we integrate chess as one element out of many that supports the children on their way to explore their inner and outer world. Many studies show the profound benefits of chess and the effectiveness of learning through play like instill confidence, sharpen critical thinking, boost emotional intelligence, enhance arithmetic skills and strengthen academic performance. Our mission therefore is to extend those benefits and spread the word. This innovative MINIMASTER program incluses a huge variety of behavioral and interest based activities. During the classes we offer a stimulating and widespread learning enviroment with many sensory and movement related exercises and games. With this specially designed and innovatice program we cover every aspect of your child's development covered -- from social interaction to physical activity to cognitive learning through play. Through play, children will develop the confidence, creativity, curiosity and learning skills they need for school and beyond. Our MINIMASTER program is part of our chess academy as a prelevel of our MAXIMASTER program (for kids between 6 and 9). It consists of 2 levels: prelevel 1 and prelevel 2. Through that we can focus on the development areas of each defined age group. Since we work in small groups with experienced teachers, each child can grow on its individual pace.
Our lessons offer a safe, fun and nurturing environment for kids and include interactive moments, physical movements (like chessercizes as combinations of psychomotorical exercises and chess), storytelling and guidelines for game play at each level of development. The classes feature unique play based activities, games and more.
name: Chess4kids Minimasters Program 2-5 years

description:
Mafia (known also as 'Werwolf' in Germany) is a popular social psychological strategic game. There are two teams in the game playing against each other - citizens and mafia. In the beginning of the game citizens do not know who the mafia is, and their main goal is to find it out as soon as possible, since Mafia is acting as well.

The game is a huge fun to play! Apart from that, it teaches to recognize lie, persuade others and improves rhetorical skills overall.

A real game: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ll_I_BIdD5E

category.name: games
description:
Welcome to the Zürich D&D Meetup Group! <br>

Join our Discord server for more shaneanigans.

Calling all adventurers! Let's get together to play Dungeons and Dragons in the old fashion style, pen&paper and throwing dices. Started this group to meet other roleplaying enthusiasts who would like to form a group to get together and guide your characters through endless adventures.

<br>Dungeons and Dragons is the most popular tabletop role-playing game of all time. The game is played with about 6 players. One person takes the role of storyteller, AKA the Dungeon Master, and narrates the story in a medieval fantasy world filled with magic, monsters, romance, intrigue, and adventure. The rest of the players take on the roles of individual fictional characters and explore that world, often becoming heroes in the story. The story is like a completely interactive "choose your own adventure" book. Different shaped dice are used to determine the outcome of attempted actions. <br> <br>Scheduling games of D&D is a little more complicated than just showing up for a game. There are three different ways people assemble to play D&D. <br> <br>We have the "Introductory Games" meetups that will happen on Fridays and will help create new group of players who have no experience at all or already know about the D&D system. <br>We have the "Long Campaigns" meetups that will run several times per month in order to continue a Campaign (long adventure) with the same group of players. New players can join if someone steps down from the game. <br>We have "One-Shot games" where short adventures that normally take one or two sessions will be held. <br>
name: Dungeons & Dragons Zürich
organizer.name: Víctor González

category.name: games
description:
Every week we meet to play story games together. We meet from 5:30 until 10:00 on Tuesday's at the host's house in Central Luzern, about 5 minutes walk from the Bahnhof.

Anyone who enjoys collectively telling compelling stories together is welcome. Story games are similar to traditional roleplaying games, but they sometimes have no GM, and players have a bigger hand in making narrative decisions. But no prior roleplaying experience is needed--only enthusiasm and an open mind! We play in English but do not be intimidated if English is not your first language. We play one shots of indie games like:
The Quiet Year
Microscope
Fiasco
Apocalypse World
Fate
Ten Candles

The host supplies the space, snacks and any necessary dice or stationary for the game. Feel free to bring anything you want to munch on or games you'd like to try!
name: Storytelling Roleplaying Games in Luzern

We are concerned with serious games in the sense that these games have an explicit and carefully thought-out educational purpose and are not intended to be played primarily for amusement. This does not mean that serious games are not, or should not be, entertaining.” -- Clark Abt (1970).

category.name: games
description:
I am organising this group on behalf of my husband; he is a good chess player but not so good with admin... 

He hasn't played in a while and don't get many opportunities with a heavy work schedule but I am buying him a new chess board for a Christmas present and thought to gauge interest of who would want to play against him.

Our apartment in Plainpalais is cosy and central (and he has a well-stocked bar) for an evening of chess, say, 20:30 - 22:00. In summer Bastions Park, with their outdoor boards, is a stone's through away.

Meetings proposed for once a week starting in the New Year 2017. He speaks only very little French but that can be overcome I am sure.

Let me know if you're interested!

description:
Checkmate ! You just got in love with our social networking - board gaming hybrid meetings ! 

Dear social networking fans, 

We would like to invite you all to join this group, so that we could socialise and exercise our brains during our regular board games meetings. Currently, we have a large collection of various board games, some of which are not "endemic" to Switzerland. We have an unusual custom of purchasing the board games instead of souvenir fridge magnets, when we travel. 

We are always happy to hear new ideas and suggestions from all of the Meetup community members.

P.s. Monopoly is banned, it ruins relationships and families.

description:
(English describtion see below)

Diese Gruppe ist für alle die sich gerne mit anderen Leuten an einem Tisch zusammensetzen um gemeinsam Brett-, Karten- und Würfelspiele zu spielen.

Jeder ist willkommen, egal ob Euro Gamer oder Ameritrasher, Gelegenheitsspieler oder Hardcore-Zocker, Würfelwürfler oder Kartenhalter, ... ;)

Ihr seid herzlich dazu eingeladen eure eigenen Spiele mitzubringen.

Also: Games einpacken, vorbei kommen, Leute treffen, Spaß haben!

This group is for everyone who loves to sit down at a table with other people and to play board, card and dice games together.

Everybody is welcome, no matter if you are Eurogamer or Ameritrasher, Casual or Hardcore gamer, Dice roller or Card holder ... ;)

You are welcome to bring your own games.

So: Pack your games, come by, meet people, have fun!

description:
This group is for anyone that likes to play games or hang around while others are playing games :) In fact, game designers are also welcome. The whole idea is to get together and play games! So bring your favorite games and meet some people to share in the fun.

If you are interested in coming, don't worry about bringing games. Many people will bring some. If you'd like an idea of what kinds of games people bring, check out this website. It has a data bank of all kinds of board games so you can see if something there might interest you and maybe can request it from the group (keep in mind many on the top 100 are no longer in print)

Players range from casual gamers who come mostly just to have a good time and interact with others to more serious board game hobbyists.

description:
Culture Class CH <br>

Culture Class CH is all about appreciating and celebrating the diversity of life together. <br>

We do so by get togethers and having drinks in bars and clubs, but also with a handful at home. Moreover, we offer stage to exchange and learn something new. Learn about wine tasting, presentation skills, negotiation skills, or body language at home or somewhere else in an inviting atmosphere, followed (or accompanied) by some drinks. <br>

The fun of learning together won't get lost in too much seriousness. If you are having anything you would like to share, or any requests or suggestions: please contact Peter or Anna and we'll make it happen together!

<br> Culture Club CH workshops are powered by cultureclass.ch. Please 'like' us on facebook: www.facebook.org/cultureclass and we'll spoonfeed you with the best of social and clinical psychology, intercultural knowhow, and many other things worth knowing. <br>
name: Culture Club ZH

description:
Purpose: To promote the quizzing culture and regularly hold quizzes in Zurich 


Who should join: This is a group for anyone interested in trivia, facts, quizzes and to learn through fun games! As a keen enthusiast for learning, I felt there is no better and enjoyable way than 'quizzing'. This group encourages individuals or teams to conduct quizzes. 


Why:  The mind of a group is always greater than that of an individual. This group aims to have the members meet at a 'cool' place periodically and immerse in the fun world of  quizzing, trivial pursuit on any of the topics! 


What can members expect: Members can expect regular quizzes. A great opportunity to meet like-minded people and exchange knowledge, experience and have fun at different locations in Zurich!

category.name: games
description:
Chess4kids is expert in teaching chess to kids 4 years up. We work in a systematic and interactive way. Through our journey of teaching we developed a playful program that fosters children between 2 and 5 years. As a part of our learning program we integrate chess as one element out of many that supports the children on their way to explore their inner and outer world. Many studies show the profound benefits of chess and the effectiveness of learning through play like instill confidence, sharpen critical thinking, boost emotional intelligence, enhance arithmetic skills and strengthen academic performance. Our mission therefore is to extend those benefits and spread the word. This innovative MINIMASTER program incluses a huge variety of behavioral and interest based activities. During the classes we offer a stimulating and widespread learning enviroment with many sensory and movement related exercises and games. With this specially designed and innovatice program we cover every aspect of your child's development covered -- from social interaction to physical activity to cognitive learning through play. Through play, children will develop the confidence, creativity, curiosity and learning skills they need for school and beyond. Our MINIMASTER program is part of our chess academy as a prelevel of our MAXIMASTER program (for kids between 6 and 9). It consists of 2 levels: prelevel 1 and prelevel 2. Through that we can focus on the development areas of each defined age group. Since we work in small groups with experienced teachers, each child can grow on its individual pace.
Our lessons offer a safe, fun and nurturing environment for kids and include interactive moments, physical movements (like chessercizes as combinations of psychomotorical exercises and chess), storytelling and guidelines for game play at each level of development. The classes feature unique play based activities, games and more.
name: Chess4kids Minimasters Program 2-5 years

description:
Mafia (known also as 'Werwolf' in Germany) is a popular social psychological strategic game. There are two teams in the game playing against each other - citizens and mafia. category.name: games
description:
Welcome to the Zürich D&D Meetup Group! <br>

Join our Discord server for more shaneanigans.

Calling all adventurers! Let's get together to play Dungeons and Dragons in the old fashion style, pen&paper and throwing dices. Started this group to meet other roleplaying enthusiasts who would like to form a group to get together and guide your characters through endless adventures.

<br>Dungeons and Dragons is the most popular tabletop role-playing game of all time. The game is played with about 6 players. One person takes the role of storyteller, AKA the Dungeon Master, and narrates the story in a medieval fantasy world filled with magic, monsters, romance, intrigue, and adventure. The rest of the players take on the roles of individual fictional characters and explore that world, often becoming heroes in the story. The story is like a completely interactive "choose your own adventure" book. Different shaped dice are used to determine the outcome of attempted actions. <br> <br>Scheduling games of D&D is a little more complicated than just showing up for a game. There are three different ways people assemble to play D&D. <br> <br>We have the "Introductory Games" meetups that will happen on Fridays and will help create new group of players who have no experience at all or already know about the D&D system. <br>We have the "Long Campaigns" meetups that will run several times per month in order to continue a Campaign (long adventure) with the same group of players. New players can join if someone steps down from the game. <br>We have "One-Shot games" where short adventures that normally take one or two sessions will be held. <br>
name: Dungeons & Dragons Zürich
organizer.name: Víctor González

description:
Culture Class CH <br>

Culture Class CH is all about appreciating and celebrating the diversity of life together. <br>

We do so by get togethers and having drinks in bars and clubs, but also with a handful at home. Moreover, we offer stage to exchange and learn something new. Learn about wine tasting, presentation skills, negotiation skills, or body language at home or somewhere else in an inviting atmosphere, followed (or accompanied) by some drinks. <br>

The fun of learning together won't get lost in too much seriousness. If you are having anything you would like to share, or any requests or suggestions: please contact Peter or Anna and we'll make it happen together!

<br> Culture Club CH workshops are powered by cultureclass.ch. Please 'like' us on facebook: www.facebook.org/cultureclass and we'll spoonfeed you with the best of social and clinical psychology, intercultural knowhow, and many other things worth knowing. <br>

description:
Chess4kids is expert in teaching chess to kids 4 years up. We work in a systematic and interactive way. Through our journey of teaching we developed a playful program that fosters children between 2 and 5 years. As a part of our learning program we integrate chess as one element out of many that supports the children on their way to explore their inner and outer world. Many studies show the profound benefits of chess and the effectiveness of learning through play like instill confidence, sharpen critical thinking, boost emotional intelligence, enhance arithmetic skills and strengthen academic performance. Our mission therefore is to extend those benefits and spread the word. This innovative MINIMASTER program incluses a huge variety of behavioral and interest based activities. During the classes we offer a stimulating and widespread learning enviroment with many sensory and movement related exercises and games. With this specially designed and innovatice program we cover every aspect of your child's development covered -- from social interaction to physical activity to cognitive learning through play. Through play, children will develop the confidence, creativity, curiosity and learning skills they need for school and beyond. Our MINIMASTER program is part of our chess academy as a prelevel of our MAXIMASTER program (for kids between 6 and 9). It consists of 2 levels: prelevel 1 and prelevel 2. Through that we can focus on the development areas of each defined age group. Since we work in small groups with experienced teachers, each child can grow on its individual pace.
Our lessons offer a safe, fun and nurturing environment for kids and include interactive moments, physical movements (like chessercizes as combinations of psychomotorical exercises and chess), storytelling and guidelines for game play at each level of development. The classes feature unique play based activities, games and more.
name: Chess4kids Minimasters Program 2-5 years

category.name: games
description:
Welcome to the Zürich D&D Meetup Group! <br>

Join our Discord server for more shaneanigans.

Calling all adventurers! Let's get together to play Dungeons and Dragons in the old fashion style, pen&paper and throwing dices. Started this group to meet other roleplaying enthusiasts who would like to form a group to get together and guide your characters through endless adventures.

<br>Dungeons and Dragons is the most popular tabletop role-playing game of all time. The game is played with about 6 players. One person takes the role of storyteller, AKA the Dungeon Master, and narrates the story in a medieval fantasy world filled with magic, monsters, romance, intrigue, and adventure. The rest of the players take on the roles of individual fictional characters and explore that world, often becoming heroes in the story. The story is like a completely interactive "choose your own adventure" book. Different shaped dice are used to determine the outcome of attempted actions. <br> <br>Scheduling games of D&D is a little more complicated than just showing up for a game. There are three different ways people assemble to play D&D. <br> <br>We have the "Introductory Games" meetups that will happen on Fridays and will help create new group of players who have no experience at all or already know about the D&D system. <br>We have the "Long Campaigns" meetups that will run several times per month in order to continue a Campaign (long adventure) with the same group of players. New players can join if someone steps down from the game. <br>We have "One-Shot games" where short adventures that normally take one or two sessions will be held. <br>
name: Dungeons & Dragons Zürich
organizer.name: Víctor González

We do so by get togethers and having drinks in bars and clubs, but also with a handful at home. Moreover, we offer stage to exchange and learn something new. Learn about wine tasting, presentation skills, negotiation skills, or body language at home or somewhere else in an inviting atmosphere, followed (or accompanied) by some drinks. <br>

The fun of learning together won't get lost in too much seriousness. If you are having anything you would like to share, or any requests or suggestions: please contact Peter or Anna and we'll make it happen together!

<br> Culture Club CH workshops are powered by cultureclass.ch. Please 'like' us on facebook: www.facebook.org/cultureclass and we'll spoonfeed you with the best of social and clinical psychology, intercultural knowhow, and many other things worth knowing. <br>

category.name: games
description:
Chess4kids is expert in teaching chess to kids 4 years up. We work in a systematic and interactive way. Through our journey of teaching we developed a playful program that fosters children between 2 and 5 years. As a part of our learning program we integrate chess as one element out of many that supports the children on their way to explore their inner and outer world. Many studies show the profound benefits of chess and the effectiveness of learning through play like instill confidence, sharpen critical thinking, boost emotional intelligence, enhance arithmetic skills and strengthen academic performance. Our mission therefore is to extend those benefits and spread the word. This innovative MINIMASTER program incluses a huge variety of behavioral and interest based activities. During the classes we offer a stimulating and widespread learning enviroment with many sensory and movement related exercises and games. With this specially designed and innovatice program we cover every aspect of your child's development covered -- from social interaction to physical activity to cognitive learning through play. Through play, children will develop the confidence, creativity, curiosity and learning skills they need for school and beyond. Our MINIMASTER program is part of our chess academy as a prelevel of our MAXIMASTER program (for kids between 6 and 9). It consists of 2 levels: prelevel 1 and prelevel 2. Through that we can focus on the development areas of each defined age group. Since we work in small groups with experienced teachers, each child can grow on its individual pace.
Our lessons offer a safe, fun and nurturing environment for kids and include interactive moments, physical movements (like chessercizes as combinations of psychomotorical exercises and chess), storytelling and guidelines for game play at each level of development. The classes feature unique play based activities, games and more.
name: Chess4kids Minimasters Program 2-5 years

category.name: games
description:
Mafia (known also as 'Werwolf' in Germany) is a popular social psychological strategic game. There are two teams in the game playing against each other - citizens and mafia. In the beginning of the game citizens do not know who the mafia is, and their main goal is to find it out as soon as possible, since Mafia is acting as well.

The game is a huge fun to play! Apart from that, it teaches to recognize lie, persuade others and improves rhetorical skills overall.

A real game: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ll_I_BIdD5E

category.name: games
description:
Welcome to the Zürich D&D Meetup Group! <br>

Join our Discord server for more shaneanigans.

Calling all adventurers! Let's get together to play Dungeons and Dragons in the old fashion style, pen&paper and throwing dices. Started this group to meet other roleplaying enthusiasts who would like to form a group to get together and guide your characters through endless adventures.

<br>Dungeons and Dragons is the most popular tabletop role-playing game of all time. The game is played with about 6 players. One person takes the role of storyteller, AKA the Dungeon Master, and narrates the story in a medieval fantasy world filled with magic, monsters, romance, intrigue, and adventure. The rest of the players take on the roles of individual fictional characters and explore that world, often becoming heroes in the story. The story is like a completely interactive "choose your own adventure" book. Different shaped dice are used to determine the outcome of attempted actions. <br> <br>Scheduling games of D&D is a little more complicated than just showing up for a game. There are three different ways people assemble to play D&D. <br> <br>We have the "Introductory Games" meetups that will happen on Fridays and will help create new group of players who have no experience at all or already know about the D&D system. <br>We have the "Long Campaigns" meetups that will run several times per month in order to continue a Campaign (long adventure) with the same group of players. New players can join if someone steps down from the game. <br>We have "One-Shot games" where short adventures that normally take one or two sessions will be held. <br>
name: Dungeons & Dragons Zürich

category.name: games
description:
Every week we meet to play story games together. We meet from 5:30 until 10:00 on Tuesday's at the host's house in Central Luzern, about 5 minutes walk from the Bahnhof.

Anyone who enjoys collectively telling compelling stories together is welcome. Story games are similar to traditional roleplaying games, but they sometimes have no GM, and players have a bigger hand in making narrative decisions. But no prior roleplaying experience is needed--only enthusiasm and an open mind! We play in English but do not be intimidated if English is not your first language. We play one shots of indie games like:
The Quiet Year
Microscope
Fiasco
Apocalypse World
Fate
Ten Candles

The host supplies the space, snacks and any necessary dice or stationary for the game. Feel free to bring anything you want to munch on or games you'd like to try!
name: Storytelling Roleplaying Games in Luzern
organizer.name: Willem

description:
This group is for anyone that likes to play games or hang around while others are playing games :) In fact, game designers are also welcome. The whole idea is to get together and play games! So bring your favorite games and meet some people to share in the fun.

If you are interested in coming, don't worry about bringing games. Many people will bring some. If you'd like an idea of what kinds of games people bring, check out this website. It has a data bank of all kinds of board games so you can see if something there might interest you and maybe can request it from the group (keep in mind many on the top 100 are no longer in print)

Players range from casual gamers who come mostly just to have a good time and interact with others to more serious board game hobbyists.

description:
Purpose: To promote the quizzing culture and regularly hold quizzes in Zurich 


Who should join: This is a group for anyone interested in trivia, facts, quizzes and to learn through fun games! As a keen enthusiast for learning, I felt there is no better and enjoyable way than 'quizzing'. This group encourages individuals or teams to conduct quizzes. 


Why:  The mind of a group is always greater than that of an individual. This group aims to have the members meet at a 'cool' place periodically and immerse in the fun world of  quizzing, trivial pursuit on any of the topics! 


What can members expect: Members can expect regular quizzes. A great opportunity to meet like-minded people and exchange knowledge, experience and have fun at different locations in Zurich!
name: Zurich Quiz Meetup - Qwizzeria

category.name: games
description:
Chess4kids is expert in teaching chess to kids 4 years up. We work in a systematic and interactive way. Through our journey of teaching we developed a playful program that fosters children between 2 and 5 years. As a part of our learning program we integrate chess as one element out of many that supports the children on their way to explore their inner and outer world. Many studies show the profound benefits of chess and the effectiveness of learning through play like instill confidence, sharpen critical thinking, boost emotional intelligence, enhance arithmetic skills and strengthen academic performance. Our mission therefore is to extend those benefits and spread the word. This innovative MINIMASTER program incluses a huge variety of behavioral and interest based activities. During the classes we offer a stimulating and widespread learning enviroment with many sensory and movement related exercises and games. With this specially designed and innovatice program we cover every aspect of your child's development covered -- from social interaction to physical activity to cognitive learning through play. Through play, children will develop the confidence, creativity, curiosity and learning skills they need for school and beyond. Our MINIMASTER program is part of our chess academy as a prelevel of our MAXIMASTER program (for kids between 6 and 9). It consists of 2 levels: prelevel 1 and prelevel 2. Through that we can focus on the development areas of each defined age group. Since we work in small groups with experienced teachers, each child can grow on its individual pace.
Our lessons offer a safe, fun and nurturing environment for kids and include interactive moments, physical movements (like chessercizes as combinations of psychomotorical exercises and chess), storytelling and guidelines for game play at each level of development. The classes feature unique play based activities, games and more.
name: Chess4kids Minimasters Program 2-5 years

description: Hey game creators! If you create your own game and want it to succeed, it's really important that you test it regularly. I've create this group because my friend and I are looking for testers for our game project. But we noticed that there has not yet been created a space for this very purpose only in Zürich. "Game Design Testing" lets you test your game, play others' games and get feedback to prepare it for the market ;) You are welcome if you are a gamer or any kind of game creator.

category.name: games
description:
Mafia (known also as 'Werwolf' in Germany) is a popular social psychological strategic game. There are two teams in the game playing against each other - citizens and mafia. In the beginning of the game citizens do not know who the mafia is, and their main goal is to find it out as soon as possible, since Mafia is acting as well.

The game is a huge fun to play! Apart from that, it teaches to recognize lie, persuade others and improves rhetorical skills overall.

A real game: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ll_I_BIdD5E
name: Zürich Mafia-game Meetup

category.name: games
description:
Welcome to the Zürich D&D Meetup Group! <br>

Join our Discord server for more shaneanigans.

Calling all adventurers! Let's get together to play Dungeons and Dragons in the old fashion style, pen&paper and throwing dices. Started this group to meet other roleplaying enthusiasts who would like to form a group to get together and guide your characters through endless adventures.

<br>Dungeons and Dragons is the most popular tabletop role-playing game of all time. The game is played with about 6 players. One person takes the role of storyteller, AKA the Dungeon Master, and narrates the story in a medieval fantasy world filled with magic, monsters, romance, intrigue, and adventure. The rest of the players take on the roles of individual fictional characters and explore that world, often becoming heroes in the story. The story is like a completely interactive "choose your own adventure" book. Different shaped dice are used to determine the outcome of attempted actions. <br> <br>Scheduling games of D&D is a little more complicated than just showing up for a game. There are three different ways people assemble to play D&D. <br> <br>We have the "Introductory Games" meetups that will happen on Fridays and will help create new group of players who have no experience at all or already know about the D&D system. <br>We have the "Long Campaigns" meetups that will run several times per month in order to continue a Campaign (long adventure) with the same group of players. New players can join if someone steps down from the game. <br>We have "One-Shot games" where short adventures that normally take one or two sessions will be held. <br>
name: Dungeons & Dragons Zürich
organizer.name: Víctor González

description:
This group is for anyone that likes to play games or hang around while others are playing games :) In fact, game designers are also welcome. The whole idea is to get together and play games! So bring your favorite games and meet some people to share in the fun.

If you are interested in coming, don't worry about bringing games. Many people will bring some. If you'd like an idea of what kinds of games people bring, check out this website. It has a data bank of all kinds of board games so you can see if something there might interest you and maybe can request it from the group (keep in mind many on the top 100 are no longer in print)

Players range from casual gamers who come mostly just to have a good time and interact with others to more serious board game hobbyists.

category.name: games
description:
Culture Class CH <br>

Culture Class CH is all about appreciating and celebrating the diversity of life together. <br>

We do so by get togethers and having drinks in bars and clubs, but also with a handful at home. Moreover, we offer stage to exchange and learn something new. Learn about wine tasting, presentation skills, negotiation skills, or body language at home or somewhere else in an inviting atmosphere, followed (or accompanied) by some drinks. <br>

The fun of learning together won't get lost in too much seriousness. If you are having anything you would like to share, or any requests or suggestions: please contact Peter or Anna and we'll make it happen together!

<br> Culture Club CH workshops are powered by cultureclass.ch. Please 'like' us on facebook: www.facebook.org/cultureclass and we'll spoonfeed you with the best of social and clinical psychology, intercultural knowhow, and many other things worth knowing. <br>

description:
Purpose: To promote the quizzing culture and regularly hold quizzes in Zurich 


Who should join: This is a group for anyone interested in trivia, facts, quizzes and to learn through fun games! As a keen enthusiast for learning, I felt there is no better and enjoyable way than 'quizzing'. This group encourages individuals or teams to conduct quizzes. 


Why:  The mind of a group is always greater than that of an individual. This group aims to have the members meet at a 'cool' place periodically and immerse in the fun world of  quizzing, trivial pursuit on any of the topics! 


What can members expect: Members can expect regular quizzes. A great opportunity to meet like-minded people and exchange knowledge, experience and have fun at different locations in Zurich!

category.name: games
description:
Chess4kids is expert in teaching chess to kids 4 years up. We work in a systematic and interactive way. Through our journey of teaching we developed a playful program that fosters children between 2 and 5 years. As a part of our learning program we integrate chess as one element out of many that supports the children on their way to explore their inner and outer world. Many studies show the profound benefits of chess and the effectiveness of learning through play like instill confidence, sharpen critical thinking, boost emotional intelligence, enhance arithmetic skills and strengthen academic performance. Our mission therefore is to extend those benefits and spread the word. This innovative MINIMASTER program incluses a huge variety of behavioral and interest based activities. During the classes we offer a stimulating and widespread learning enviroment with many sensory and movement related exercises and games. With this specially designed and innovatice program we cover every aspect of your child's development covered -- from social interaction to physical activity to cognitive learning through play. Through play, children will develop the confidence, creativity, curiosity and learning skills they need for school and beyond. Our MINIMASTER program is part of our chess academy as a prelevel of our MAXIMASTER program (for kids between 6 and 9). It consists of 2 levels: prelevel 1 and prelevel 2. Through that we can focus on the development areas of each defined age group. Since we work in small groups with experienced teachers, each child can grow on its individual pace.
Our lessons offer a safe, fun and nurturing environment for kids and include interactive moments, physical movements (like chessercizes as combinations of psychomotorical exercises and chess), storytelling and guidelines for game play at each level of development. The classes feature unique play based activities, games and more.
name: Chess4kids Minimasters Program 2-5 years

description: Hey game creators! If you create your own game and want it to succeed, it's really important that you test it regularly. description:
Mafia (known also as 'Werwolf' in Germany) is a popular social psychological strategic game. There are two teams in the game playing against each other - citizens and mafia. In the beginning of the game citizens do not know who the mafia is, and their main goal is to find it out as soon as possible, since Mafia is acting as well.

The game is a huge fun to play! Apart from that, it teaches to recognize lie, persuade others and improves rhetorical skills overall.

A real game: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ll_I_BIdD5E

category.name: games
description:
Welcome to the Zürich D&D Meetup Group! <br>

Join our Discord server for more shaneanigans.

Calling all adventurers! Let's get together to play Dungeons and Dragons in the old fashion style, pen&paper and throwing dices. Started this group to meet other roleplaying enthusiasts who would like to form a group to get together and guide your characters through endless adventures.

<br>Dungeons and Dragons is the most popular tabletop role-playing game of all time. The game is played with about 6 players. One person takes the role of storyteller, AKA the Dungeon Master, and narrates the story in a medieval fantasy world filled with magic, monsters, romance, intrigue, and adventure. The rest of the players take on the roles of individual fictional characters and explore that world, often becoming heroes in the story. The story is like a completely interactive "choose your own adventure" book. Different shaped dice are used to determine the outcome of attempted actions. <br> <br>Scheduling games of D&D is a little more complicated than just showing up for a game. There are three different ways people assemble to play D&D. <br> <br>We have the "Introductory Games" meetups that will happen on Fridays and will help create new group of players who have no experience at all or already know about the D&D system. <br>We have the "Long Campaigns" meetups that will run several times per month in order to continue a Campaign (long adventure) with the same group of players. New players can join if someone steps down from the game. <br>We have "One-Shot games" where short adventures that normally take one or two sessions will be held. <br>
name: Dungeons & Dragons Zürich
organizer.name: Víctor González

category.name: games
description:
Every week we meet to play story games together. We meet from 5:30 until 10:00 on Tuesday's at the host's house in Central Luzern, about 5 minutes walk from the Bahnhof.

Anyone who enjoys collectively telling compelling stories together is welcome. Story games are similar to traditional roleplaying games, but they sometimes have no GM, and players have a bigger hand in making narrative decisions. But no prior roleplaying experience is needed--only enthusiasm and an open mind! We play in English but do not be intimidated if English is not your first language. We play one shots of indie games like:
The Quiet Year
Microscope
Fiasco
Apocalypse World
Fate
Ten Candles

The host supplies the space, snacks and any necessary dice or stationary for the game. Feel free to bring anything you want to munch on or games you'd like to try!
name: Storytelling Roleplaying Games in Luzern

category.name: games
description:
Every week we meet to play story games together. We meet from 5:30 until 10:00 on Tuesday's at the host's house in Central Luzern, about 5 minutes walk from the Bahnhof.

Anyone who enjoys collectively telling compelling stories together is welcome. Story games are similar to traditional roleplaying games, but they sometimes have no GM, and players have a bigger hand in making narrative decisions. But no prior roleplaying experience is needed--only enthusiasm and an open mind! We play in English but do not be intimidated if English is not your first language. We play one shots of indie games like:
The Quiet Year
Microscope
Fiasco
Apocalypse World
Fate
Ten Candles

The host supplies the space, snacks and any necessary dice or stationary for the game. Feel free to bring anything you want to munch on or games you'd like to try!
name: Storytelling Roleplaying Games in Luzern
organizer.name: Willem

description:
This group is for anyone that likes to play games or hang around while others are playing games :) In fact, game designers are also welcome. The whole idea is to get together and play games! So bring your favorite games and meet some people to share in the fun.

If you are interested in coming, don't worry about bringing games. Many people will bring some. If you'd like an idea of what kinds of games people bring, check out this website. It has a data bank of all kinds of board games so you can see if something there might interest you and maybe can request it from the group (keep in mind many on the top 100 are no longer in print)

Players range from casual gamers who come mostly just to have a good time and interact with others to more serious board game hobbyists.

description:
Culture Class CH <br>

Culture Class CH is all about appreciating and celebrating the diversity of life together. <br>

We do so by get togethers and having drinks in bars and clubs, but also with a handful at home. Moreover, we offer stage to exchange and learn something new. Learn about wine tasting, presentation skills, negotiation skills, or body language at home or somewhere else in an inviting atmosphere, followed (or accompanied) by some drinks. <br>

The fun of learning together won't get lost in too much seriousness. If you are having anything you would like to share, or any requests or suggestions: please contact Peter or Anna and we'll make it happen together!

<br> Culture Club CH workshops are powered by cultureclass.ch. Please 'like' us on facebook: www.facebook.org/cultureclass and we'll spoonfeed you with the best of social and clinical psychology, intercultural knowhow, and many other things worth knowing. <br>
name: Culture Club ZH

Why:  The mind of a group is always greater than that of an individual. This group aims to have the members meet at a 'cool' place periodically and immerse in the fun world of  quizzing, trivial pursuit on any of the topics! 


What can members expect: Members can expect regular quizzes. A great opportunity to meet like-minded people and exchange knowledge, experience and have fun at different locations in Zurich!

category.name: games
description:
Chess4kids is expert in teaching chess to kids 4 years up. We work in a systematic and interactive way. Through our journey of teaching we developed a playful program that fosters children between 2 and 5 years. As a part of our learning program we integrate chess as one element out of many that supports the children on their way to explore their inner and outer world. Many studies show the profound benefits of chess and the effectiveness of learning through play like instill confidence, sharpen critical thinking, boost emotional intelligence, enhance arithmetic skills and strengthen academic performance. Our mission therefore is to extend those benefits and spread the word. This innovative MINIMASTER program incluses a huge variety of behavioral and interest based activities. During the classes we offer a stimulating and widespread learning enviroment with many sensory and movement related exercises and games. With this specially designed and innovatice program we cover every aspect of your child's development covered -- from social interaction to physical activity to cognitive learning through play. Through play, children will develop the confidence, creativity, curiosity and learning skills they need for school and beyond. Our MINIMASTER program is part of our chess academy as a prelevel of our MAXIMASTER program (for kids between 6 and 9). It consists of 2 levels: prelevel 1 and prelevel 2. Through that we can focus on the development areas of each defined age group. Since we work in small groups with experienced teachers, each child can grow on its individual pace.
Our lessons offer a safe, fun and nurturing environment for kids and include interactive moments, physical movements (like chessercizes as combinations of psychomotorical exercises and chess), storytelling and guidelines for game play at each level of development. The classes feature unique play based activities, games and more.
name: Chess4kids Minimasters Program 2-5 years

Your travels across the multiverse have lead you here to the Magic Meetup group Zürich. The group is open to any format. Once there are some members we can decide where and when to meet. If you want to be an event organizer too, please write a message to the admin.

Now hit that join-button and fill in the poll what formats you like to play so we can find out which formats shall be hosted first. Also join the discussion in the respective section.

Let's hope for some wild MTG-action soon!

category.name: games
description:
Mafia (known also as 'Werwolf' in Germany) is a popular social psychological strategic game. There are two teams in the game playing against each other - citizens and mafia. In the beginning of the game citizens do not know who the mafia is, and their main goal is to find it out as soon as possible, since Mafia is acting as well.

The game is a huge fun to play! Apart from that, it teaches to recognize lie, persuade others and improves rhetorical skills overall.

A real game: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ll_I_BIdD5E

category.name: games
description:
Welcome to the Zürich D&D Meetup Group! <br>

Join our Discord server for more shaneanigans.

Calling all adventurers! Let's get together to play Dungeons and Dragons in the old fashion style, pen&paper and throwing dices. Started this group to meet other roleplaying enthusiasts who would like to form a group to get together and guide your characters through endless adventures.

<br>Dungeons and Dragons is the most popular tabletop role-playing game of all time. The game is played with about 6 players. One person takes the role of storyteller, AKA the Dungeon Master, and narrates the story in a medieval fantasy world filled with magic, monsters, romance, intrigue, and adventure. The rest of the players take on the roles of individual fictional characters and explore that world, often becoming heroes in the story. The story is like a completely interactive "choose your own adventure" book. Different shaped dice are used to determine the outcome of attempted actions. <br> <br>Scheduling games of D&D is a little more complicated than just showing up for a game. There are three different ways people assemble to play D&D. <br> <br>We have the "Introductory Games" meetups that will happen on Fridays and will help create new group of players who have no experience at all or already know about the D&D system. <br>We have the "Long Campaigns" meetups that will run several times per month in order to continue a Campaign (long adventure) with the same group of players. New players can join if someone steps down from the game. <br>We have "One-Shot games" where short adventures that normally take one or two sessions will be held. <br>
name: Dungeons & Dragons Zürich
organizer.name: Víctor González

description:
This group is for anyone that likes to play games or hang around while others are playing games :) In fact, game designers are also welcome. The whole idea is to get together and play games! So bring your favorite games and meet some people to share in the fun.

If you are interested in coming, don't worry about bringing games. Many people will bring some. If you'd like an idea of what kinds of games people bring, check out this website. It has a data bank of all kinds of board games so you can see if something there might interest you and maybe can request it from the group (keep in mind many on the top 100 are no longer in print)

Players range from casual gamers who come mostly just to have a good time and interact with others to more serious board game hobbyists.

description:
Culture Class CH <br>

Culture Class CH is all about appreciating and celebrating the diversity of life together. <br>

We do so by get togethers and having drinks in bars and clubs, but also with a handful at home. Moreover, we offer stage to exchange and learn something new. Learn about wine tasting, presentation skills, negotiation skills, or body language at home or somewhere else in an inviting atmosphere, followed (or accompanied) by some drinks. <br>

The fun of learning together won't get lost in too much seriousness. If you are having anything you would like to share, or any requests or suggestions: please contact Peter or Anna and we'll make it happen together!

<br> Culture Club CH workshops are powered by cultureclass.ch. Please 'like' us on facebook: www.facebook.org/cultureclass and we'll spoonfeed you with the best of social and clinical psychology, intercultural knowhow, and many other things worth knowing. <br>
name: Culture Club ZH

Purpose: To promote the quizzing culture and regularly hold quizzes in Zurich 


Who should join: This is a group for anyone interested in trivia, facts, quizzes and to learn through fun games! As a keen enthusiast for learning, I felt there is no better and enjoyable way than 'quizzing'. This group encourages individuals or teams to conduct quizzes. 


Why:  The mind of a group is always greater than that of an individual. This group aims to have the members meet at a 'cool' place periodically and immerse in the fun world of  quizzing, trivial pursuit on any of the topics! 


What can members expect: Members can expect regular quizzes. A great opportunity to meet like-minded people and exchange knowledge, experience and have fun at different locations in Zurich!

category.name: games
description:
Chess4kids is expert in teaching chess to kids 4 years up. We work in a systematic and interactive way. Through our journey of teaching we developed a playful program that fosters children between 2 and 5 years. As a part of our learning program we integrate chess as one element out of many that supports the children on their way to explore their inner and outer world. Many studies show the profound benefits of chess and the effectiveness of learning through play like instill confidence, sharpen critical thinking, boost emotional intelligence, enhance arithmetic skills and strengthen academic performance. Our mission therefore is to extend those benefits and spread the word. This innovative MINIMASTER program incluses a huge variety of behavioral and interest based activities. During the classes we offer a stimulating and widespread learning enviroment with many sensory and movement related exercises and games. With this specially designed and innovatice program we cover every aspect of your child's development covered -- from social interaction to physical activity to cognitive learning through play. Through play, children will develop the confidence, creativity, curiosity and learning skills they need for school and beyond. Our MINIMASTER program is part of our chess academy as a prelevel of our MAXIMASTER program (for kids between 6 and 9). It consists of 2 levels: prelevel 1 and prelevel 2. Through that we can focus on the development areas of each defined age group. Since we work in small groups with experienced teachers, each child can grow on its individual pace.
Our lessons offer a safe, fun and nurturing environment for kids and include interactive moments, physical movements (like chessercizes as combinations of psychomotorical exercises and chess), storytelling and guidelines for game play at each level of development. The classes feature unique play based activities, games and more.
name: Chess4kids Minimasters Program 2-5 years

category.name: games
description:
Mafia (known also as 'Werwolf' in Germany) is a popular social psychological strategic game. There are two teams in the game playing against each other - citizens and mafia. In the beginning of the game citizens do not know who the mafia is, and their main goal is to find it out as soon as possible, since Mafia is acting as well.

The game is a huge fun to play! Apart from that, it teaches to recognize lie, persuade others and improves rhetorical skills overall.

A real game: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ll_I_BIdD5E
name: Zürich Mafia-game Meetup

category.name: games
description:
Welcome to the Zürich D&D Meetup Group! <br>

Join our Discord server for more shaneanigans.

Calling all adventurers! Let's get together to play Dungeons and Dragons in the old fashion style, pen&paper and throwing dices. Started this group to meet other roleplaying enthusiasts who would like to form a group to get together and guide your characters through endless adventures.

<br>Dungeons and Dragons is the most popular tabletop role-playing game of all time. The game is played with about 6 players. One person takes the role of storyteller, AKA the Dungeon Master, and narrates the story in a medieval fantasy world filled with magic, monsters, romance, intrigue, and adventure. The rest of the players take on the roles of individual fictional characters and explore that world, often becoming heroes in the story. The story is like a completely interactive "choose your own adventure" book. Different shaped dice are used to determine the outcome of attempted actions. <br> <br>Scheduling games of D&D is a little more complicated than just showing up for a game. There are three different ways people assemble to play D&D. <br> <br>We have the "Introductory Games" meetups that will happen on Fridays and will help create new group of players who have no experience at all or already know about the D&D system. <br>We have the "Long Campaigns" meetups that will run several times per month in order to continue a Campaign (long adventure) with the same group of players. New players can join if someone steps down from the game. <br>We have "One-Shot games" where short adventures that normally take one or two sessions will be held. <br>
name: Dungeons & Dragons Zürich
organizer.name: Víctor González

category.name: games
description:
Every week we meet to play story games together. We meet from 5:30 until 10:00 on Tuesday's at the host's house in Central Luzern, about 5 minutes walk from the Bahnhof.

Anyone who enjoys collectively telling compelling stories together is welcome. Story games are similar to traditional roleplaying games, but they sometimes have no GM, and players have a bigger hand in making narrative decisions. But no prior roleplaying experience is needed--only enthusiasm and an open mind! We play in English but do not be intimidated if English is not your first language. We play one shots of indie games like:
The Quiet Year
Microscope
Fiasco
Apocalypse World
Fate
Ten Candles

The host supplies the space, snacks and any necessary dice or stationary for the game. Feel free to bring anything you want to munch on or games you'd like to try!
name: Storytelling Roleplaying Games in Luzern

description:
This group is for anyone that likes to play games or hang around while others are playing games :) In fact, game designers are also welcome. The whole idea is to get together and play games! So bring your favorite games and meet some people to share in the fun.

If you are interested in coming, don't worry about bringing games. Many people will bring some. If you'd like an idea of what kinds of games people bring, check out this website. It has a data bank of all kinds of board games so you can see if something there might interest you and maybe can request it from the group (keep in mind many on the top 100 are no longer in print)

Players range from casual gamers who come mostly just to have a good time and interact with others to more serious board game hobbyists.

description:
Culture Class CH <br>

Culture Class CH is all about appreciating and celebrating the diversity of life together. <br>

We do so by get togethers and having drinks in bars and clubs, but also with a handful at home. Moreover, we offer stage to exchange and learn something new. Learn about wine tasting, presentation skills, negotiation skills, or body language at home or somewhere else in an inviting atmosphere, followed (or accompanied) by some drinks. <br>

The fun of learning together won't get lost in too much seriousness. If you are having anything you would like to share, or any requests or suggestions: please contact Peter or Anna and we'll make it happen together!

<br> Culture Club CH workshops are powered by cultureclass.ch. Please 'like' us on facebook: www.facebook.org/cultureclass and we'll spoonfeed you with the best of social and clinical psychology, intercultural knowhow, and many other things worth knowing. <br>
name: Culture Club ZH

category.name: games
description:
Chess4kids is expert in teaching chess to kids 4 years up. We work in a systematic and interactive way. Through our journey of teaching we developed a playful program that fosters children between 2 and 5 years. As a part of our learning program we integrate chess as one element out of many that supports the children on their way to explore their inner and outer world. Many studies show the profound benefits of chess and the effectiveness of learning through play like instill confidence, sharpen critical thinking, boost emotional intelligence, enhance arithmetic skills and strengthen academic performance. Our mission therefore is to extend those benefits and spread the word. This innovative MINIMASTER program incluses a huge variety of behavioral and interest based activities. During the classes we offer a stimulating and widespread learning enviroment with many sensory and movement related exercises and games. With this specially designed and innovatice program we cover every aspect of your child's development covered -- from social interaction to physical activity to cognitive learning through play. Through play, children will develop the confidence, creativity, curiosity and learning skills they need for school and beyond. Our MINIMASTER program is part of our chess academy as a prelevel of our MAXIMASTER program (for kids between 6 and 9). It consists of 2 levels: prelevel 1 and prelevel 2. Through that we can focus on the development areas of each defined age group. Since we work in small groups with experienced teachers, each child can grow on its individual pace.
Our lessons offer a safe, fun and nurturing environment for kids and include interactive moments, physical movements (like chessercizes as combinations of psychomotorical exercises and chess), storytelling and guidelines for game play at each level of development. The classes feature unique play based activities, games and more.
name: Chess4kids Minimasters Program 2-5 years

category.name: games
description:
Mafia (known also as 'Werwolf' in Germany) is a popular social psychological strategic game. There are two teams in the game playing against each other - citizens and mafia. In the beginning of the game citizens do not know who the mafia is, and their main goal is to find it out as soon as possible, since Mafia is acting as well.

The game is a huge fun to play! Apart from that, it teaches to recognize lie, persuade others and improves rhetorical skills overall.

A real game: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ll_I_BIdD5E

category.name: games
description:
Welcome to the Zürich D&D Meetup Group! <br>

Join our Discord server for more shaneanigans.

Calling all adventurers! Let's get together to play Dungeons and Dragons in the old fashion style, pen&paper and throwing dices. Started this group to meet other roleplaying enthusiasts who would like to form a group to get together and guide your characters through endless adventures.

<br>Dungeons and Dragons is the most popular tabletop role-playing game of all time. The game is played with about 6 players. One person takes the role of storyteller, AKA the Dungeon Master, and narrates the story in a medieval fantasy world filled with magic, monsters, romance, intrigue, and adventure. The rest of the players take on the roles of individual fictional characters and explore that world, often becoming heroes in the story. The story is like a completely interactive "choose your own adventure" book. Different shaped dice are used to determine the outcome of attempted actions. <br> <br>Scheduling games of D&D is a little more complicated than just showing up for a game. There are three different ways people assemble to play D&D. <br> <br>We have the "Introductory Games" meetups that will happen on Fridays and will help create new group of players who have no experience at all or already know about the D&D system. <br>We have the "Long Campaigns" meetups that will run several times per month in order to continue a Campaign (long adventure) with the same group of players. New players can join if someone steps down from the game. <br>We have "One-Shot games" where short adventures that normally take one or two sessions will be held. <br>
name: Dungeons & Dragons Zürich
organizer.name: Víctor González

category.name: games
description:
Every week we meet to play story games together. We meet from 5:30 until 10:00 on Tuesday's at the host's house in Central Luzern, about 5 minutes walk from the Bahnhof.

Anyone who enjoys collectively telling compelling stories together is welcome. Story games are similar to traditional roleplaying games, but they sometimes have no GM, and players have a bigger hand in making narrative decisions. But no prior roleplaying experience is needed--only enthusiasm and an open mind! We play in English but do not be intimidated if English is not your first language. We play one shots of indie games like:
The Quiet Year
Microscope
Fiasco
Apocalypse World
Fate
Ten Candles

The host supplies the space, snacks and any necessary dice or stationary for the game. Feel free to bring anything you want to munch on or games you'd like to try!
name: Storytelling Roleplaying Games in Luzern

description:
This group is for anyone that likes to play games or hang around while others are playing games :) In fact, game designers are also welcome. The whole idea is to get together and play games! So bring your favorite games and meet some people to share in the fun.

If you are interested in coming, don't worry about bringing games. Many people will bring some. If you'd like an idea of what kinds of games people bring, check out this website. It has a data bank of all kinds of board games so you can see if something there might interest you and maybe can request it from the group (keep in mind many on the top 100 are no longer in print)

Players range from casual gamers who come mostly just to have a good time and interact with others to more serious board game hobbyists.

description:
Culture Class CH <br>

Culture Class CH is all about appreciating and celebrating the diversity of life together. <br>

We do so by get togethers and having drinks in bars and clubs, but also with a handful at home. Moreover, we offer stage to exchange and learn something new. Learn about wine tasting, presentation skills, negotiation skills, or body language at home or somewhere else in an inviting atmosphere, followed (or accompanied) by some drinks. <br>

The fun of learning together won't get lost in too much seriousness. If you are having anything you would like to share, or any requests or suggestions: please contact Peter or Anna and we'll make it happen together!

<br> Culture Club CH workshops are powered by cultureclass.ch. Please 'like' us on facebook: www.facebook.org/cultureclass and we'll spoonfeed you with the best of social and clinical psychology, intercultural knowhow, and many other things worth knowing. <br>

category.name: games
description:
Chess4kids is expert in teaching chess to kids 4 years up. We work in a systematic and interactive way. Through our journey of teaching we developed a playful program that fosters children between 2 and 5 years. As a part of our learning program we integrate chess as one element out of many that supports the children on their way to explore their inner and outer world. Many studies show the profound benefits of chess and the effectiveness of learning through play like instill confidence, sharpen critical thinking, boost emotional intelligence, enhance arithmetic skills and strengthen academic performance. Our mission therefore is to extend those benefits and spread the word. This innovative MINIMASTER program incluses a huge variety of behavioral and interest based activities. During the classes we offer a stimulating and widespread learning enviroment with many sensory and movement related exercises and games. With this specially designed and innovatice program we cover every aspect of your child's development covered -- from social interaction to physical activity to cognitive learning through play. Through play, children will develop the confidence, creativity, curiosity and learning skills they need for school and beyond. Our MINIMASTER program is part of our chess academy as a prelevel of our MAXIMASTER program (for kids between 6 and 9). It consists of 2 levels: prelevel 1 and prelevel 2. Through that we can focus on the development areas of each defined age group. Since we work in small groups with experienced teachers, each child can grow on its individual pace.
Our lessons offer a safe, fun and nurturing environment for kids and include interactive moments, physical movements (like chessercizes as combinations of psychomotorical exercises and chess), storytelling and guidelines for game play at each level of development. The classes feature unique play based activities, games and more.
name: Chess4kids Minimasters Program 2-5 years
